name: tRNA-uridine 2-sulfurtransferase
reaction: a [protein]-S-sulfanyl-L-cysteine + uacil34 in tRNA + ATP + reduced acceptor = a [protein]-L-cysteine + 2-thiouracil34 in tRNA + AMP + diphosphate + acceptor
comment: The enzyme, found in bacteria, catalyses formation of the 2-thiouridine modification in the wobble position of tRNAGln, tRNALys and tRNAGlu.

references.title: MnmA and IscS are required for in vitro 2-thiouridine biosynthesis in Escherichia coli.
Mechanistic insights into sulfur relay by multiple sulfur mediators involved in thiouridine biosynthesis at tRNA wobble positions.
